description: Collecting issues #60-69 of the hit series, collecting the epochal "Good Prince" storyline. Flycatcher is drawn into the spotlight as he discovers the startling truth about his own past as the Frog Prince. At the same time, he learns that the Adversary plans to destroy his foes once and for all. How can the meek Flycatcher stop this deadly foe?
name: Volume 10

character_credits.name: The Old Woman who lived in a Shoe

first_appearance_characters.name: The Old Woman who lived in a Shoe

description: Collecting FABLES #52-59! Pinocchio suffers seriously divided loyalties between his father, the evil Adversary, and his fellow Fable refugees in New York. Plus, Bigby Wolf reluctantly decides it's finally time to square accounts with his long-estranged father, the North Wind, and makes a journey with Snow White and their kids to find him.
name: Volume 9

character_credits.name: The Old Woman who lived in a Shoe

first_appearance_characters.name: The Old Woman who lived in a Shoe

description: Collecting issues #48-51 of writer and creator Bill Willingham's award-winning Vertigo series, WOLVES also includes newly-created maps of Fabletown and the Homelands illustrated by Willingham and, as a special bonus, Willingham's complete script to the double-sized issue #50.
name: Volume 8

description: Collecting issues #42-47 of writer Bill Willingham's Eisner Award-winning creation, FABLES: ARABIAN NIGHTS (AND DAYS) opens a new front in the struggle between the Fables and the Adversary as the worlds of the Arabian Fables are invaded — leading to an unprecedented diplomatic mission to Fabletown and a bad case of culture shock! This seventh volume of the popular Vertigo series also includes "The Ballad of Rodney and June," the 2-part story of forbidden love among the Adversary's wooden soldiers, and features stellar Art by Mark Buckingham, Steve Leialoha, Jim Fern, Jimmy Palmiotti and Andrew Pepoy.
name: Volume 7

character_credits.name: The Old Woman who lived in a Shoe

first_appearance_characters.name: The Old Woman who lived in a Shoe

description: Collecting issues #34-41 of writer Bill Willingham's Eisner Award-winning creation, HOMELANDS follows Boy Blue on a mission of revenge as he uncovers the Adversary's true identity! Plus, the 2-part story of Jack's adventures in Hollywood and the one-shot story of Mowgli's return to Fabletown.
name: Volume 6

description:
If you thought the SOS Brigade’s adventures couldn’t get any more outrageous…you’ve never met Haruhi-chan! Nagato has gone otaku! Asakura is her pint-size prisoner/plaything! Mikuru’s so cute she turns into a sheep! You’ll find plenty of gags and guffaws as Haruhi dives into the world of four-panel and short comics!!

Story Titles

  • The SOS Brigade Takes the Stage
  • Nagato Becomes An Otaku
  • Capturing Achakura-san
  • The "All Hope Is Lost" Pose
  • Nagato & Tsuruya vs. Santa
  • Mikuru the Sheep Debuts In A Chaotic First Dream of the Year
  • Mori-san Makes A Shocking First Appearance
  • Kyon and Koizumii Become Hosts
  • An Infinity Lion Comes Calling
  • Trying Out Mail-Order Shopping
name: Vol. 1

description:
Thought Alita's struggles were finally over? Hoped she could settle down with her devoted full-flesh man in a nice house in the Scrapyard suburbs? Think again!

Alita awakens in a new cyborg body--as stunning as before, but even more powerful--in a world whose dark secret has at long last been revealed to all, pitting parent against child, metal against flesh....

Disregarding the ending of the original Battle Angel Alita volume, the story of Alita has her resurrected by Desty Nova, for maniacal and scientific reasons. Alita must battle the remaining AR series members that have survived, and have developed unique personalities of their own.
name: Angel Reborn

description:
The final, apocalyptic battle between the epic heroes and the boss of all boss monsters ended quite badly for the people of Mati'aca. Now people with 'S-skill' (the stuff of heroes) are the only defense the ravaged and scattered settlements have from the monsters who have taken over the world. Mad Max meets Final Fantasy in this incredible, action-packed one-shot creation from Fred Perry!

An action-packed one shot from Fred Perry, artist and creator of Gold Digger, and Legacy. In the war between the heroes and the monsters. The monsters have won out. The world is thrown into chaos, and the only ones that can save the lands of Mati'aca are those with the "S-Skill", the Stuff of Heroes.
name: S-Guild

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, inker, colorist, cover, other

description:
Stories: 
1. The Mummy's Hand (Evans) 
2.  The Ghost Ship (Wood)
3.  The Flaming Scar (Williamson)
4.  The Phantom Visitor (Bolle) 
5. The Woman In The Tomb (Bolle)
6. Message From Beyond (Giolitti)
name: True Ghost Stories

description:
The Utopian city of Tiphares' diabolical secret is out, pitting parent against child, metal against flesh! As the reluctant protector of a surviving band of innocents, recently resurrected cyborg Alita must stop a rampaging three-story-high robot with the mind of a three-year-old child! But all she really wants to do is find her long-lost friends from one of her many other lives....

Alita must battle a giant robot with the mind of a child. She also finds a purpose: to find the brain bio-chip of her old friend, Lou, and bring her back to life.
name: Angel of the Innocents

description:
Alita arrives on space station Ketheres to rescue her friend Lou's brain, which has been stolen and plugged into a vast array powering an A.I. known as "Melchizedek"! Before Alita can get over her culture shock, she gets embroiled in the vicious squabbles of a league of planets who have harnessed the secret of immortality itself!

Alita travels to the space city of Ketheres(tethered to Tiphares and in orbit around Earth) to find the brain bio-chip of her friend, Lou, which is being used to help power a massive A.I. called Melchizedek. Alita finds that space and the planets are populated by many people, robots and varioius political parties.
name: Angel Eternal

description: Next on the adventure list is the hunt for the Lost City of Atlantis in the Hitchhiker's Guide to Lost Cities. The Digger Sisters are going down on the deep blue with Penny, Stripe, and the whole gang joining this time. Oh,.....that didn't sound right. Here's hoping there wont be any uninvited guests.
name: Hitchhiker's Guide to the Lost Cities Part II

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, inker, cover, other

description:
Batman and Spiderman team up to take on villains Kingpin and Ras Al Ghul.

Spider-man is a wise-cracking but compassionate man who has an overwhelming sense of responsibility. Batman is a dark, menacing figure with no super-powers. Kingpin is a scheming, criminal mastermind and Ras Al Ghul is a self-proclaimed visionary and savior who believes the path to salvation involves rebuilding the world after nearly wiping out its population.

The Demon plans once again to upset the balance of the earth. He approaches Wilson Fisk, believing that the Kingpin can finally help him realize his ideal. However, betrayal is very likely with these two. What will happen when they team up?
name: New Age Dawning

description:
FINAL BATTLE - OR CERTAIN SUICIDE?

Still battling a mysterious alien virus, Superman gathers his waning strength for one last effort to stop the mad plans of the genocidal Dr. Ward. But while the Man of Steel battles his way into the madman's stronghold, a deadly Predator from another world is stalking him...

Collecting issues 22 and 28-33 of the hit VERTIGO series, this trade paperback features two tales of Bigby's exploits during World War II as well as "The Year After," which follows the aftermath of the Adversary's attempt to conquer Fabletown — including the birth of Snow White and Bigby's children!
name: Volume 5

character_credits.name: Doctor Sieglinde von Abensberg und Traun
The Cow who Jumped over the Moon
The Old Woman who lived in a Shoe

first_appearance_characters.name: Doctor Sieglinde von Abensberg und Traun
The Cow who Jumped over the Moon
The Old Woman who lived in a Shoe

description: Kyle Baker may well be the funniest man in comics. With books like The Cowboy Wally Show, Why I Hate Saturn, Plastic Man, and The Bakers on his resume, along with four (of his eight) Eisner Awards in the "Best Writer/Artist Humor" category, it's hard to argue against him. But he does serious, too—and you can't get much more serious than Nat Turner. He is the all-around cartoonist—he can write, pencil, ink, and color with the best of them. His work has appeared in such diverse publications as The New York Times, Esquire, Rolling Stone, and Mad. Without question, Kyle Baker is a Modern Master, and this book presents a career-spanning interview and discussion of his creative process, plus plenty of rare and unseen art, including an 8-page color section, and a gallery of commissioned work!
name: Kyle Baker

character_credits.name: Queen of the Leather Astro-Girls of Saturn

first_appearance_characters.name: Queen of the Leather Astro-Girls of Saturn

description:
What do you do when your city is under siege from a riot, your personal war against the 'Blue Lights' has spun into all-out chaos, and all the good choices are long since gone? If you're Alice Hotwire, you risk everything to face the horror of Amir Malik and uncover a truth that could both save the city - and destroy it at the same time.

The riots are coming to a head and Alice appears drowned in the facility.

An unconscious Alice dreams of her parents and the technological upbringing she had. Her mother was a beautiful scientist and her dad a software genius who would make video blogs ranting about the society which ultimately leads to government agency raiding their facility calling them terrorists. Alice and her mother were playing a video game with handheld light guns and when the armed counter-terrorist team enter they mistake it for a real gun and kill her mother.

She wakes live and before the skull and ribcage being again. It is Malik the innocent man buried as a murderer. He used his power to get into Glenn's mind and he was given 10 times as much attention and work as the others they worked on. He used tentacles to save Alice from the flood waters and now he is going to the police HQ. He floats out of the facility and Alice scrambles for the transporter to take her back there too. She called Peter and directs him there as well, his car gets snarled up in rioting yobs who recognize him a s cop. before they can do him any harm a homeland enforcement drone arrives over his car and opens fire without warning smashing the mob into a fiery pulp. They ID him as a cop and tell him they are clearing the roads into the city and he should get indoors.

fearing for their lives the uniformed officers decide to hand over the pair to the mob, much to the new commander's anger. As she races outside to stop the handover both the DHE and the ghost-bomb arrive. Alice is worried when Peter tells her the drones are clearing the roads, its not how they deal with riots.. but it is if they need heavy weapons to deal with the ghostbomb.

Dr Love has worked out that Mailk has been using the blue-light to transmit a signal that enrages people and caused all the trouble they have been seeing. Malik was killed during Enhanced Questioning where police tortured him and buried him as a guilty man. Now he wants revenge for 30 years being buried with the worst in society.

the drones take out the DHE craft that suppressing communications and Hotwire downloads the schematics and manuals for the equipment used to make the tentacled body of Malik and wirelessly hacks his physical boy using default passwords. She explained before how all devices interconnect and self test and secure each other, but since his equipment was top-secret they excluded that from him but ironically left the very back-doors that cloud of safety prevents. This stops his physical form from attacking but his control fo the blue light is still in full effect. She jams a suppressor spike into him and is shrouded in flames, Peter races to her aid as Malik begs her not to do this and not to hurt herself. Peter jumps in an pulls her away, her arm on fire and her face burnt down the right side but Malik is finally put to rest. Elsewhere there is just two bloody marks where the bad cops were standing.
name: Skull Face

description:
Kyle takes Donna to California to meet his mother.

Kyle is visiting the Alex's grave and thinks about all that's happened since he got the ring. While there he runs into Alex's sister who is incredibly upset at him for missing the funeral.

She slaps him and tells him that he has no right to be there and that he'd better not come back. He says good-bye to Alex and takes off with Donna to L.A. to visit his mom.

He tells Donna that he hasn't been on good terms with his mom for quite a while, that she never treated him like he was an adult and he hasn't talked to her since he got the ring.

En route to his mom's place, he stops a fire at Star Labs, where Donna accuses him of stalling. When he finally gets to his mom's house, she asks to see the costume, which surprises Kyle, but she just tells him that a mother can tell these things.

While trying to catch up on things, Kyle mentions that he tried to find his father, which sends his mom over the edge. Apparently, that was something they never talked about, and this starts a fight between the two and ends with Kyle walking out.

The issue ends back in Star Labs with some computer equipment building itself into "The Machine Messiah" as it calls itself.
name: Go Home Again

description: Bill Willingham's runaway hit series FABLES continues its success in this fourth trade paperback, collecting issues #19-21 and #23-27 (issue #22 will appear in a future collection) and featuring the rise of a new threat to Fabletown. Also included is the Prestige Format Special Fables: The Last Castle. When Little Red Riding Hood suddenly walks through the gate between this world and the lost Fable Homelands, she's welcomed as a miraculous survivor by nearly everyone - everyone except her old nemesis, Bigby Wolf, who smells spying and subversion more than survival. But will he be able to prove his case before disaster strikes? And how will it all affect Prince Charming's upstart campaign to become the new mayor of Fabletown?
name: Volume 4

character_credits.name: The Cow who Jumped over the Moon

first_appearance_characters.name: The Cow who Jumped over the Moon

volume.name: Fables: March of the Wooden Soldiers

description: Marvel's 70th Anniversary is explored in this issue.

Lovely Battle Angel Alita entered the Zenith of Things Tournament to liberate her friend Lou's brain from enslavement as a computer component, but to accomplish her goal she must defeat a team with an even worthier cause! As if this ethical dilemma weren't tough enough, a nasty ghost in her ear won't stop questioning her every motive...

Plus, pint-size yet scrappy Sechs gets a surpirsing new cyborg body with rather--er--different equipment!

In order to liberate her old friend, Lou's, brain, Alita and her new-found friends continue in the Zenith of Things fighting tournament. Sechs is given a new cyborg body, getting a sex-change in the process!
name: Haunted Angel

description:
While lovely cyborg Alita's allies battle real, personal, and existential demons in the Z.O.T. Tournament in hopes of distracting government forces long enough for Alita to rescue her friend Lou's brain from enslavement as a computer component, the deepest secrets of Alita's former life are finally revealed!

But sometimes it's better not to know the truth about your past--especially when you're the one responsible for the horror of everyone's present...

Alita leaves the fighting in the Zenith of Things fighting tournament to her allies while she goes searching for the brain bio-chip of her old friend, Lou. She finds startling, murderous revelations of her past, when she was known as Yoko.
name: Guilty Angel

description:
Our heroine, beautiful cyborg Alita, has finally penetrated the center of Melchizedek, the supercomputer who is holding her friend Lou's brain hostage. There she is transfixed by a vivid vision of the undead life of Caerula. As the waking dream continues to unfold, Alita learns the secret behind the origin of the Scrapyard where she was reborn, humanity's journey to the stars, and the awesome responsibility that has been entrusted to her...

Continuing as a vision of the past, the narrative continues to tell the story of the ancient vampire, Caerula. The origin story of Tiphares, the Scrapyard, and man's journey into space are here.
name: Angel's Duty

description:
Alita stages a unique protest to save children from becoming cannon fodder, joins forces with some unlikely allies to compete in a sporting event whose promoters have ulterior motives, and, well...dies!

In order to save a group of orphans, Alita must fight in a grand fighting tournament whose purpose is not what it seems.
name: Angel of Protest

description:
Competing in the rigged Z.O.T. Tournament in hopes of rescuing her friend Lou's brain from enslavement as a computer component, lovely cyborg Alita is locked into a battle to the death with a vampire! But how does one kill the undead!? Also, Master hacker Ping's alliance of convenience with Alita pays off beyond his wildest dreams; mad scientist Desty Nova makes a reappearance (of sorts); and an encounter with strangers raises a disturbing possibility about Alita's mysterious past....

Alita continues her battle against an ancient vampire in the Zenith of Things fighting tournament. Alita also makes a frightening discovery about her past as a Panzer Kunst fighter from Mars.
name: The Angel & The Vampire

description:
Lovely cyborg Alita and her allies dive into the center of Melchizedek, the super computer that is holding her friend Lou's brain hostage as one of its organic components. There, Alita witnesses a vivid vision of the undead life of her recent battlefield opponent, the mysterious vampire Caerula, who presented her with the key to Melchizedek's kingdom...

Alita enters the massive AI structure Melchizedek with the key given to her by the vampire, Caerula. The narrative, as Alita's vision, takes place 200 years prior. Earth was forced into an ice-age because of a meteor strike, virtually eradicating the human species but for a few. Vampires have survived however, and under the leadership of Victor they feed on the remaining humans.
name: Angel's Vision

description:
Our heroine, beautiful cyborg Alita, has finally penetrated the center of Melchizedek, the supercomputer who is holding her friend Lou's brain hostage. Now ancient vampire Vilma asks her to accept an awesome responsibility, while Alita's copies fight their own battles on the outside, and her archenemy, mad scientist Desty Nova, returns. And returns. And returns! Is there no end to him? And whose side is he, or he, or he on, anyway??? Then, a moment of weakness may cost Alita everything…!

Having witnessed the vision of this universe's origin, Alita is given the Fata Morgana, the key to shutting down Melchizedek, the computer that enslaves the bio-chip brains of everyone from Tiphares.
name: Angel Goes Nova

description:
What is Alita's fate...? A doomed opponent in battle with Sechs may reveal some clues. Meanwhile, senseis and students fight for supremacy. Their mystical techniques can slay a tiger and even a dragon. But moves of such power may only be used against an opponent who is truly worthy!

Sechs continues fighting in the Zenith of Things fighting tournament. In the oddest issue yet, Sechs must fight a large phallic robot.
name: Angel Cake

description:
In 2021 Earth is a far uglier place. Most humans are on Mars but Deckard's back home, among the wretched. See San Francisco as its denizens try to live in the aftereffect of World War Terminus.

If they think human life is hard, try being an android among the masses!

volume.name: Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?

description: Zodiac's master plan escalates to dizzying heights during Dark Reign. First up: a horrific act of super-villain terrorism that involves a group of iconic Marvel heroes! Next: a planet-wide threat that will test Norman Osborn's leadership abilities like no other has! And what does Galactus have to do with all of this? The new wave of Marvel villains has finally arrived!
name: Ill-Gotten Gains

description: While Romeo makes a valiant attempt to recover from being burnt to a crisp, Whisper lies dying and unprotected from the undead assailants seeking her. Romeo is really blowing this whole "saving Whisper from certain death because I love her" thing. He'd better get his act together quick or we're not gonna have a 6th issue...
name: Helter Skelter Romance, Act 5: They Love

description: A new softcover collecting the acclaimed FABLES #11-18, including the 4-part "Storybook Love." Also included are the 2-part "A Sharp Operator" and the single-issue tales "Bag o' Bones" and "Barleycorn Brides." Don't miss this amazing third collection, topped off with a stunning new wraparound cover by James Jean.
name: Volume 3

description: The Clap contends with a deadly death trap, has a pleasant drink at the hotel bar, lets their internal tensions come to a head, finds that backstage security isn't all it's cracked up to be, and learns that in their line of work, "Everybody Wants You (Dead)!"
name: Chapter 3: Everybody Wants You (Dead)

description: Genn and Britanny are both out for the count as Gina alone faces the curse with a body, now calling itself Grave Digger. When her enemy has all of her weapons. Gina must use her mind to prevail, and keep it low enough to keep her head from getting blown off.
name: Curse, Part 4

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, inker, cover, other

description: Collecting FABLES #6-10, the second story arc of the fan-favorite, critically acclaimed VERTIGO series. Travel to upstate New York, where the non-human Fable characters have found refuge on a farm, miles from mankind. But all is not well on the farm — and a conspiracy to free them from the shackles of their perceived imprisonment may lead to a war that could wrest control of the Fables community away from Snow White. Starring Goldilocks and the Three Bears. Plus, a sketchbook section featuring art by Willingham, Buckingham and Jean.
name: Volume 2

character_credits.name: The Cow who Jumped over the Moon
The Old Woman who lived in a Shoe

first_appearance_characters.name: The Old Woman who lived in a Shoe
The Cow who Jumped over the Moon

description: The entire Diggers household - Theodore, Julia, Gina, Cheetah, Brianna, Genn and Seance, plus Stripe and Ryan - visit the Retreat, an artificial paradise inhabited by the magical creatures of Earth. While Seance and Ryan face off in what begins as a friendly game of volleyball, Cheetah and Stripe encounter a pack of were-cats, including Garfield, whom Cheetah met on Jade. Garfield professes his love for Cheetah, prompting Stripe to challenge him; meanwhile, a series of misunderstandings leads to a showdown between Seance and Ryan. The elder Diggers break up both situations, and while the showdown for Gina remains unresolved, Garfield realizes Cheetah loves only Stripe. He leaves the two alone... and Stripe finally proposes to Cheetah.

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description: Gina, Ryan, Penny, and Charlotte continue to explore Civ-Alpha, while Cheetah observes the arrival on the surface of the Montara twins plus Pee Wee and his thugs. As Cheetah briefly fights Daishi, the four below discover the city was inhabited by two races, the Saurians and the Beta-Phantoms. In the upper caves, a Beta-Phantom absorbs the male Montara twin and quickly overwhelms Pee Wee's group until Cheetah arrives to protect them. On Jade, Brianna and Sheila go for a morning bath. Tirga is already there but Sheila chases him off. Sheila tries to warn Brianna about Tirga's womanizing and accidentally knocks Brianna unconscious when she won't listen. This jogs something from the back of Brianna's mind... and Grave Digger returns.

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

concept_credits.name: Were Races in the Gold Digger Universe

first_appearance_concepts.name: Were Races in the Gold Digger Universe

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover, other

description:
In the same vein as best-selling "fractured-fairy-tales" such as Wicked and Confessions of an Ugly Stepsister is Bill Willingham's runaway hit graphic novel series FABLES. No longer just children's tales, Willingham has created a new world for these beloved fables...one that exists within our own. When a savage creature known only as the Adversary conquered the fabled lands of legends and fairy tales, all of the infamous inhabitants of folklore were forced into exile. Disguised among the normal citizens of modern-day New York, these magical characters created their own secret society-within an exclusive luxury apartment building on Manhattan's Upper West Side-called Fabletown. But when Snow White's party-girl sister, Rose Red, is apparently murdered, it is up to Bigby, Fabletown's sheriff, and a reformed and pardoned Big Bad Wolf, to determine if the culprit is Bluebeard, Rose's ex-lover and notorious wife killer, or Jack, her current live-in boyfriend and former beanstalk-climber.

General Notes

A new edition of the trade was released May 16, 2012 featuring a new cover by Mark Buckingham and some new back-up material.
name: Volume 1

concept_credits.name: Were Races in the Gold Digger Universe

first_appearance_concepts.name: Were Races in the Gold Digger Universe

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover, other

description:
In one day on Jade: Brianna goes to trial for all the chaos using technology in a magical society, Gets sentenced and sent to jail, Gets busted out by her cellmate,...And then succeeds in bringing Raphael back??? 
 
Only the begining of this issue as the Super Villian Tirant unveils his greatest plan to concuer Jade-realm.

concept_credits.name: Were Races in the Gold Digger Universe

first_appearance_concepts.name: Were Races in the Gold Digger Universe

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover, other

description: Gina, Cheetah, and Julia recover at an inn where they meet Julia's student, the were-jaguar Gar Silvear. Brendan defeats Sander and Thabian while tracking the Magic Sapper, but then Cheetah confronts him for killing her clan. At the last second, Brendan acquires the artifact and great power. Dr. Diggers arrives with backup, but the Magic Sapper drains him and the other spell-casters of their powers. Natasha and Vladimir observe all this from the Realm of the Undead and piece together most of the Lich-King's plan, but they are arrested soon after.
name: The Lich-King, Part 3

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description: With Brendan destroyed, the Lich-King must take a direct hand in the battle for Gina. He quickly defeats everyone still at the Magic Observatory, captures Gina, and returns to the Realm of the Undead to await Dr. Diggers. Dr. Diggers follows his undead father alone, and the two duel for the life of Gina. Natasha and Vlad manage to free Gina, and her interference allows Dr. Diggers to strip the Lich-King of power once and for all.
name: The Lich-King, Part 5

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description: As the heroes prepare to leave Jade (and Tark and Mesha decide to remain at the Magic Observatory), Gina and Cheetah go grocery shopping... only to encounter the leprechauns again. After many attempts, the leprechauns capture the Diggers sisters and rush them through a farcical trial. Only by exploiting a particular weakness of fairies - their magic is useless against felines - do the two manage to escape death. The leprechauns apologize and promise never to do it again.

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description: Gina manages to lay her hands on the Key of Aton, passport to an ancient Egyptian underground airport... for about five seconds, before Ryan Tabbot snatches it and beats her to the site. After Gina inadvertently rescues Ryan from a trap in the complex, the two team up to explore the place. The complex, originally a hyperspace junction-point, has been inactive for 2700 years, but the alien caretaker is still awake, and he snatches the Key and attempts to return the complex to his home world. Through Gina and Ryan's efforts, the alien is foiled... but the complex and its treasures are destroyed. Not all is lost, however; Gina and Ryan are going out on Friday night...

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description: Gina, Cheetah, and Brianna seek out the invisible tower of the Dragon Pharaoh... and encounter the power-hungry Selena Masters. After much ado with each other, the traps of the tower, and the various evil beings imprisoned within (whom Brianna attacks while they are unable to use their native powers), both sides finally reach the Dragon Orb in the center of the tower. When Selena removes the orb, the inmates are released, and only quick action by Cheetah saves them from horrid fates.

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description: With everyone's safe return from Aebra, the countdown is started for Cheetah's postponed wedding. As guests (including the dreaded in-laws) arrive and final preparations are made, Tanya plans to stop the wedding cold... with the appearance of another were-cheetah, the male Raphiel. The wedding is saved at the last moment thanks to some Barbarian friends and a magic wedding dress.

The battle between Brianna and her alter ego Grave Digger continues... and more of Seer's Hamlet is destroyed in the process, starting with Nali's hut. G'nolga and Hanzo use the distraction to capture more mages. As Gaja tries to stop G'nolga, Grave Digger turns Brianna's peebos against her. Hanzo steals one of Nali's potion that she intended for Sheila, but he finds drinking it has life-altering consequences. Hanzo has trouble dealing with his changes, but uses his new "attributes" to defeat Tirga and escape with the captured mages. Gaja's and Gnolga's fight seems to end in mutual defeat, but Hanzo comes back briefly to rescue G'nolga. Genn gets into Grave Digger's head to show her demons are her own making. This allows Grave Digger and Brianna to come to terms and merge back together. Unfortunately, Gaja's wounds prove too serious for his were-cat healing and he is dying...

description:
After the wedding of the year, And things are starting to settle down. Stripe's trying his hand at BBQ, Brittany is relaxing while directing Gina's  workbots (Super Construction Votoms) in the building of the second story add-on to the house she shares with her sister, And Gina and Penny are back from the Appraisers with the cash recieved from their last adventure.

Or has it?  
 
Who is Agent M? And what does he want with Stripe?  Who are these Were-Rats? And why are they spying on the Diggers household? Now that Penny and Gina have a handle on Beta technology, what do they do with it? And Why is Brianna sneaking around? Things are shaping up to the kind of adventures you Don't go looking for in this issue of Gold Digger.

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover, other

description:
Brianna decides to go on a rescue mission to Jade-Realm, to save Raphiel.  
Genn is along to help, with Seance providing the transportation - what could go wrong?   
Answer: Trouble spelled G'nolga.

 
Meanwhile - Brittany continues to try to remove the bell collar and Penny calls on Gina to come back out to Civ - Alpha to help with a mystery.

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover, other

description:
On Jade, Array and Tirant reveal that they are stealing mages for a reason. Meanwhile, Sheila is afraid she has made Brianna lose her memory, and Brianna is using even more magic now. While Gar and Sheila try to figure out what is wrong with Brianna, Genn arrives and senses that the Grave Digger curse is back in control. The Edge Guard try to stop her, but Brianna only surrenders when Genn threatens to go into her mind.

On Earth, Cheetah barely defeats the Beta-Phatom in time as she later learns when Charlotte lets slip that if the beta ring is overcharged it will explode along with whoever is using it. As Penny and Gina take turns babsitting a reviving a Saurian, another Beta-Phantom attacks... but is stopped by the awakened Saurian "robot".

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover, other

description: Brianna in a coma, being examined by a team  of magicusers and a doctor? The EdgeGuard in trouble with the local law? The aftermath of the return of GraveDigger continues.

description: Gina's future self, intent on finding a way to prevent the disaster in her past, presents her younger self with a new warp core computer OS, then bids her goodbye. Young Gina returns to Earth and, with her new insight into Artificer tech, compiles all her relic data and resolves to return to Uhm di Turrok, which has already been located by a group called Team Elite. Meanwhile, Madrid furthers her plans, having Genn and Dao fashion her the perfect Gina disguise.

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Penny and Charlotte visit an ancient Olmec crypt in the Amazon jungles, but discover that a few competitors have already staked claims on sections of the site. No one can enter without Penny's key, though, so the two are very closely watched. Penny's glad they don't know she also has a crypt map revealing where Montezuma hid his true treasures from Cortez...

Charlotte fails to mention the small totem she's picked up during her and Penny's South American expedition. When Penny discovers that the totem of Taquatital has pulled in two older Charlottes from two completely different alternate futures, she know's Charlie's really screwed up this time...

description: Barbra "Crush" Duncan, a hero coerced into villainy, has almost paid her debt to society. Her good friend Danielle "The Avenger" Carter comes from NYC to the Federal Meta-Detention Center in Florida for her release. However, Crime Syndicate X stage a massive prison siege that same day, leaving Barbra and Danielle trapped inside. Luckily, Agency Zero agents 'Gia and Xane are there too...

person_credits.name: Fred Perry
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, inker, colorist, cover

description: To aid the Lich-King's plan to replace his currently weakening body with that of Gina, he sends Brendan to retrieve the Magic Sapper hidden somewhere on Jade. Meanwhile Gina and Cheetah attempt to escape Rook's fortress in Jade, and Julia arrives and works her way through the fortress' defenses. Julia defeats Rook just as the sisters succeed in breaking free.
name: The Lich-King, Part 2

description: Tifanny, Pojo and Charlotte go with Gina on a prep school field trip to do some real-life paleontology at a real dinosaur fossil site. Charlotte finds what appears to be a fifty-pound, peanut-shaped rock, which turns out to be a Saurian egg, preserved using that lost race's technology. When the cute baby Saurian inside wakes up, the kids befriend him, but for some reason, Gina thinks Saurians are too dangerous to live. Can Tif' and company keep their new friend Houston, the last Saurian, at home without being caught?
